# MLN core (always on)

- You are working inside the **MLN Stack** (Mwixnet × LitVM × Nostr × Tor). **Always reference [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md)** for the canonical doc table and **[`PRODUCT_SPEC.md`](PRODUCT_SPEC.md)** for product intent, economics, and roadmap.
- **Foundational skills** (invoke when the task matches their descriptions): [`.cursor/skills/doc-sync/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/doc-sync/SKILL.md), [`.cursor/skills/mln-pm/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/mln-pm/SKILL.md), [`.cursor/skills/mln-web3-product-design/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/mln-web3-product-design/SKILL.md), [`.cursor/skills/coinswapd-reference/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/coinswapd-reference/SKILL.md).
- **Implementation skills** under [`.cursor/skills/`](.cursor/skills/): `mln-go-engineer`, `mln-contracts`, `mln-frontend-wails`, `mln-qa`, `mln-deployment`, `mln-observability`, `mln-architecture-diagrams` — follow the matching `SKILL.md` when editing those areas.
- **When to lean on which skill (quick routing):** Nostr wire or **`nostr/`** fixtures → **`.cursor/rules/mln-nostr-wire.mdc`** + **`research/NOSTR_MLN.md`** + **`mln-qa`**; operator logging / diagnostics → **`mln-observability`**; MWEB RPC, onion JSON, or **`research/coinswapd/`** → **`coinswapd-reference`**; Mermaid stack diagrams → **`mln-architecture-diagrams`** (citations only).
- **Multi-agent / external models:** Pairing Cursor with Grok, Gemini, or other tools — see **[`docs/AGENT_HANDOFF.md`](docs/AGENT_HANDOFF.md)** (complements the canonical table in **`AGENTS.md`**).
- **Non-trivial or cross-layer tasks:** Follow **[`CONTRIBUTING.md`](CONTRIBUTING.md)** and persist human-reviewed plans under **[`.cursor/plans/`](.cursor/plans/)** (see **[`.cursor/plans/README.md`](.cursor/plans/README.md)**).
- **Strict separation:** **MWEB** = privacy engine and default per-hop routing-fee path; **LitVM** = registry, stake, bonds, slashing, grievances (judicial layer, not happy-path mix verification); **Nostr** = discovery and gossip (not authoritative for stake); **Tor** = transport.
